# CATCH-ALL: strip .html for all regular content pages
# ============================================================================
# GSC data (2026-07-17 Coverage + Performance export) confirmed that every
# regular content page — not just the deprecated ones above — is being
# served at BOTH /page and /page.html with a 200 status, and Google is
# indexing both as separate URLs and splitting ranking signal between them
# (e.g. /bmi-calculator-kids and /bmi-calculator-kids.html both show
# meaningful separate impression counts in Search Console). Canonical tags
# have been fixed in the same patch to point at the clean URL (matching what
# the sitemap already outputs), but a canonical tag is only a hint — Google
# can still choose to index both. This explicit redirect is what actually
# forces resolution to one URL.
#
# Placed at the END of this file (after the specific deprecated-page rules
# above) so Cloudflare Pages' first-match-wins rule order lets those more
# specific rules fire first; this generic rule only catches everything else.
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT — TEST BEFORE MERGING TO PRODUCTION:
# A rule in the OPPOSITE direction (/guides -> /guides.html) previously
# caused an ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS outage on this site by fighting against
# Cloudflare Pages' own platform-level html_handling behavior. This new rule
# goes the SAME direction as that platform behavior (both strip .html), so
# it should be additive rather than conflicting — but given the site's prior
# history with exactly this class of bug, deploy this to a Cloudflare Pages
# preview branch first and manually check a few URLs (including /guides and
# /guides.html) resolve correctly with no redirect loop before merging to
# the production branch.
/*.html /:splat 301